headline: Why Arista Networks Stock Is Skyrocketing Wednesday
summary: Arista Networks Inc. (NYSE:ANET) reported better-than-expected second-quarter financial results after markets closed on Tuesday. Adjusted EPS jumped to 73 cents from 53 cents a year ago, versus estimates of 65 cents. Gross margin was 65.2% in the second quarter. headline: The AI Trade Is More Than Just Nvidia and AMD. 2 Other Stocks to Consider.
summary: Nvidia  the world’s biggest chip maker, is often described as the “pick and shovel” provider for the new technology’s massive investment story.  Earnings from  Advanced Micro Devices Arista Networks  and  Astera Labs  suggest that there are subtle ways to play the trade.  Much like the Gold Rush of the mid-19th century, where hundreds of prospectors went bust but the sellers of gold-digging equipment made a fortune, chip makers are expected to capitalize on the AI investment regardless of who emerges victorious.

headline: S&P 500 and Nasdaq lifted by earnings, Fed hopes
summary: The S&P 500 and the Nasdaq edged higher on Wednesday, buoyed by a new round of corporate earnings, while lingering hopes that the Federal Reserve will cut rates kept markets alive.  At 9:37 a.m. ET, the Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 2.89 points, or 0.01%, to 44,114.63, the S&P 500 gained 7.58 points, or 0.12%, to 6,306.64 and the Nasdaq Composite rose 43.34 points, or 0.21%, to 20,959.89.  Arista Networks soared 13.6% as the cloud networking company projected quarterly revenue above analyst estimates.
